name: MyTodoApp
tagline: Learning angularJS, breezeJS, bootstrap, sass, and express.
body:
### Inspiration
While learning how to use different javascript frameworks there's just so much cool stuff out there. 

Thanks especially too the following for their contributions and spreading the knowledge:
* Addy Osmani (@addyosmani) and [addyosmani.com](http://www.addyosmani.com)
* Dan Wahlin (@DanWahlin) and [dwahlin blog](http://weblogs.asp.net/dwahlin)
* John Pappa (@johnpapa) and [egghead.io](http://eggehad.io)
* Todd Motto (@toddmotto) and [toddmotto.com](https://toddmotto.com/)
* Kent Dodds (@kentcdodds) and [angular-formly](http://angular-formly.com/#/)
* and the rest of the crew at [devchat.tv](https://devchat.tv/)

### Why?
It's about time I get comfortable working with git, open source, and building my own portfolio in general.

### What?
Start small with getting used to git, github, open source methods/processes, and a basic angular app. 

### When?
These are loose goals, let's try to go quicker than this!
- May - get basic site setup
- June - get basic app working
- July - get full functional app working
- August - add goodness (CI/CD, ??)
- Sept - branch and upgrade to angular 2

### Authors and Contributors
So far this is just me, Chris Frantz (@frantz_chris).
